{{For|the subject|classical philology|Classics}} {{Infobox journal | title = Classical Philology | cover = CPcover.gif | discipline = [[Classics]] | abbreviation = Class. Philol. | editor = Sarah Nooter | publisher = [[University of Chicago Press]] | country = United States | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1906-present | website = http://www.journals.uchicago.edu/cp | ISSN = 0009-837X | JSTOR = 0009837x }} '''''Classical Philology''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] established in 1906. It is published by the [[University of Chicago Press]] and covers all aspects of [[Greco-Roman world|Graeco-Roman antiquity]], including literature, languages, [[anthropology]], history, social life, philosophy, religion, art, material culture, and the history of [[classical studies]]. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Sarah Nooter.
