{{Expand Belarusian|date=December 2008|Мікола Іванавіч Ермаловіч}} {{Expand Belarusian (Taraškievica)|date=December 2008|Мікола Ермаловіч}} {{Infobox writer | name = Mikola Yermalovich | native_name = Мікола Іванавіч Ермаловіч | native_name_lang = be | birth_date = {{Birth date|1921|04|29}} | birth_place = Malyja Navasiolki, [[Minsky Uyezd]], [[Byelorussian Soviet Socialist Republic|BSSR]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|2000|03|05|1921|04|29}} | death_place = [[Minsk]], [[Belarus]] | occupation = [[Opinion journalist]], [[literary scholar]], [[writer]], [[historian]] | alma_mater = [[Maxim Tank Belarusian State Pedagogical University|BSPU]] }}'''Mikola Yermalovich''' ({{lang-be|Ермало́віч Міко́ла Іва́навіч, Mikoła Jermałovič}}) (April 29, 1921 in [[Dzyarzhynsk Raion]], [[Minsk Voblast]] &ndash; March 5, 2000) — [[Belarus]]ian writer, historian. He graduated from [[Minsk Pedagogical Institute]] in 1947.
== Scientific views == Yermalovich presented the conception of history of [[Grand Duchy of Lithuania]], according to which this state was a [[Belarusians|Belarusian]], not [[Lithuanians|Baltic]].<ref>''Ермаловіч М.'' Беларуская дзяржава Вялікае княства Літоўскае. Мінск: “Беллітфонд”, 2000. —448 с. {{ref-be}}</ref>
