[[File:Museu Barbier Mueller- carrer montcada.JPG|thumb|right|Museu Barbier Mueller from Carrer Montcada]]
The '''Museu Barbier-Mueller d'Art Precolombí''' (its local name in [[Catalan language|Catalan]]; also known in {{lang-es|'''Museo Barbier-Mueller de Arte Precolombino'''}}, and in {{lang-en|'''Barbier-Mueller Pre-Columbian Art Museum'''}}) was the only [[museum]] in Europe devoted exclusively to the artistic legacy of the [[pre-Columbian]] cultures of [[the Americas]]. It was located in the [[Catalonia|Catalan]] capital of [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]]. The museum was established in 1997 to house the [[pre-Columbian art]] collection formerly held by its parent museum, the [[Barbier-Mueller Museum]] in [[Genève]], [[Switzerland]], which was loaned to the city of Barcelona. In 2012, the museum was unable to reach a purchase agreement with the collection's owner Jean Paul Barbier-Mueller. Subsequently, the world's most important Pre-Columbian collection in private hands (according to El País) was split and auctioned at Southeby's on 22 March 2013.<ref>http://ccaa.elpais.com/ccaa/2012/09/14/catalunya/1347654720_583733.html</ref>

