'''Rebecca Prichard''' (born 1971) is English author and playwright,  and one of the major contributors to the [[In-yer-face theatre]] movement.

==Biography==
Prichard studied drama at  [[Exeter University]] and in 1994, went on to her playwriting debut in 1994 in the Royal Court Young Writer's festival. In 1998 she was presented with the Critics' Circle Award for Most Promising Playwright.<ref>http://www.contemporarywriters.com/authors/?p=auth211</ref> Her play ''Essex Girls'' is regarded by playwright [[Mark Ravenhill]] as one of the best post-[[Top Girls]] all female plays.<ref>Aston, Elaine 2003, Feminist views on the English stage: women playwright, Cambridge University Press</ref>

==Selected works==
* ''Charged''
* ''Futures''
* ''Fair Game''
* ''Essex Girls''

