'''Simón Alberto Consalvi''' (7 July 1927 – 11 March 2013) was a [[Venezuela]]n politician, journalist, diplomat and historian. He was Minister of Foreign Affairs of Venezuela on two occasions (1977-1979/1985-1988), [[List of Ministers of Interior and Justice of Venezuela|Minister of Interior and Justice of Venezuela]] (1988–1989), Secretary of the Presidency (1988), and also held several Ambassadorships. A journalist and author of many books, he was member of the National Academy of History since 1997,<ref name="SC">{{es_icon}} [http://www.anhvenezuela.org/curriculo.php?cod=17 Curricular resume of Consalvi by the National Academy of History of Venezuela]</ref> and Associate Editor of the daily ''[[El Nacional (Caracas)|El Nacional]]''.
Because of a domestic accident, Simon Alberto Consalvi died in Caracas, Venezuela on 11 March 2013<ref>[http://www.eluniversal.com/nacional-y-politica/130311/fallecio-el-periodista-y-politico-simon-alberto-consalvi Falleció el periodista y político Simón Alberto Consalvi], eluniversal.com, 11 March 2013</ref> He was 85.
